WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.203 --> 00:00:06.206
(ETHEREAL CLASSICAL
MUSIC PLAYING)

2
00:02:28.216 --> 00:02:29.855
(MUSIC FADES)

3
00:02:42.835 --> 00:02:44.903
(FEET DRAGGING ON FLOOR)

4
00:02:54.407 --> 00:02:56.178
(LIGHT SWITCH CLICKS)

5
00:03:15.395 --> 00:03:19.871
The womb became the vessel
which became the cup

6
00:03:19.872 --> 00:03:22.368
that was filled
with the blood of Christ.

7
00:03:22.369 --> 00:03:24.271
Now throughout
the history of the goddess.

8
00:03:24.272 --> 00:03:28.980
we see her symbols becoming
objects for our possession.

9
00:03:29.145 --> 00:03:32.950
For example.
the Greeks decapitated Medusa

10
00:03:32.951 --> 00:03:37.384
and placed her on
Athena's shield as protection.

11
00:03:38.154 --> 00:03:39.891
Even the seats that we sit on.

12
00:03:39.892 --> 00:03:43.225
does anyone know
who it symbolizes?

13
00:03:51.772 --> 00:03:53.465
- The goddess?
- BELINDA: Yes.

14
00:03:53.466 --> 00:03:56.743
Isis's name
literally means throne.

15
00:03:56.744 --> 00:03:57.305
Is it really any wonder

16
00:03:57.306 --> 00:04:03.443
why we anthropomorphize chairs
with arm. leg. and back?

17
00:04:04.851 --> 00:04:07.986
(EERIE CLASSICAL MUSIC
PLAYING OVER RADIO)

18
00:04:10.483 --> 00:04:12.254
(DOOR OPENS)

19
00:04:12.925 --> 00:04:14.520
(DOOR CLOSES)

20
00:04:15.224 --> 00:04:16.159
- Is he in there. Mary?
- No.

21
00:04:16.160 --> 00:04:21.296
Frank will be another hour.
but you can leave him a note.

22
00:04:22.198 --> 00:04:24.199
This about the schedule.
Belinda?

23
00:04:24.200 --> 00:04:25.266
- Yes.
- Oh.

24
00:04:25.267 --> 00:04:28.170
Must feel rotten.
things out of your control.

25
00:04:28.171 --> 00:04:30.502
- Oh. I'm fine.
- Well. that's great to know

26
00:04:30.503 --> 00:04:32.471
because it's nothing personal.

27
00:04:32.472 --> 00:04:33.912
It's like. uh...

28
00:04:33.913 --> 00:04:35.815
- What does Frank call it?
- Yeah.

29
00:04:35.816 --> 00:04:38.213
Well. just tell him that
I really need to talk to him

30
00:04:38.214 --> 00:04:40.447
about the schedule. please.

31
00:04:42.317 --> 00:04:44.483
I've seen people like you
give up.

32
00:04:44.484 --> 00:04:50.160
but you're so. so good
and so valued.

33
00:04:50.259 --> 00:04:51.798
The anthropology department

34
00:04:51.799 --> 00:04:54.064
can't function without adjuncts.

35
00:04:54.065 --> 00:04:55.065
But I'm not an adjunct anymore.

36
00:04:55.066 --> 00:05:00.269
Oh. you're such a hard worker
and so smart.

37
00:05:11.379 --> 00:05:13.545
(CAR DOOR OPENS. CLOSES)

38
00:05:13.546 --> 00:05:15.823
NORMAN: Hey. Sorry I'm late.

39
00:05:16.483 --> 00:05:18.287
- Babe?
- (TAPS ON WINDOW)

40
00:05:19.222 --> 00:05:20.959
(WINDOW WHIRRING)

41
00:05:20.960 --> 00:05:21.993
Hey.

42
00:05:21.994 --> 00:05:24.424
I'm gonna throw up. Norman.
My stomach is crazy.

43
00:05:24.425 --> 00:05:28.594
Everything's fine.
Okay? Don't worry.

44
00:05:29.364 --> 00:05:32.267
What if the doctor
can't find a heartbeat?

45
00:05:32.268 --> 00:05:34.435
Hey. I love you.

46
00:05:35.403 --> 00:05:36.976
It's okay.

47
00:05:40.144 --> 00:05:42.178
(KEYBOARD AND MOUSE CLACKING)

48
00:05:42.179 --> 00:05:44.918
Your daughter looks great.
Belinda.

49
00:05:45.853 --> 00:05:47.414
Spine is aligned.

50
00:05:47.415 --> 00:05:49.922
- A nice big head.
- (BELINDA CHUCKLES)

51
00:05:49.923 --> 00:05:52.354
You see her little legs
right there?

52
00:05:53.421 --> 00:05:55.896
Now move on to the heart.

53
00:05:56.160 --> 00:05:58.964
- Can I hear it?
- Of course.

54
00:05:58.965 --> 00:06:01.935
(SOUND OF HEARTBEAT
ON SCANNER)

55
00:06:03.101 --> 00:06:05.498
It's perfect.
I can see all four...

56
00:06:05.499 --> 00:06:06.368
BELINDA: Shh.

57
00:06:06.369 --> 00:06:08.974
(HEARTBEAT CONTINUES BEATING
ON SCANNER)

58
00:06:08.975 --> 00:06:11.076
(BELINDA BREATHES DEEPLY)

59
00:06:21.416 --> 00:06:23.517
(CHAIR SCRAPING)

60
00:06:27.554 --> 00:06:30.062
(EXHALES)

61
00:06:31.558 --> 00:06:33.329
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

62
00:06:34.033 --> 00:06:35.033
NORMAN: Babe?

63
00:06:35.034 --> 00:06:37.904
Well. you said
your mother held you in it.

64
00:06:37.905 --> 00:06:39.004
Well. yeah.

65
00:06:39.005 --> 00:06:41.534
But you dragged it in here
all by yourself?

66
00:06:41.535 --> 00:06:43.173
(BELINDA SIGHS)

67
00:06:43.174 --> 00:06:44.339
Why'd I do that?

68
00:06:44.340 --> 00:06:45.913
NORMAN: Hey.

69
00:06:46.276 --> 00:06:49.510
(CHUCKLES) Hey. It's okay.

70
00:06:51.611 --> 00:06:53.382
What's going on?

71
00:06:57.584 --> 00:07:00.356
Am I supposed to be a mom?

72
00:07:03.623 --> 00:07:05.097
Yes.

73
00:07:05.361 --> 00:07:09.134
- You saw the baby.
- Yeah. I know. but...

74
00:07:09.629 --> 00:07:11.235
it's not...

75
00:07:12.401 --> 00:07:16.206
They gave away two
of my classes to a new hire.

76
00:07:16.207 --> 00:07:17.669
I'm basically losing my job.

77
00:07:17.670 --> 00:07:20.573
- They can't do that.
- Yes. they can.

78
00:07:20.574 --> 00:07:22.213
I'm non tenure.

79
00:07:22.312 --> 00:07:26.415
I knew they would always
see me as a fucking adjunct.

80
00:07:26.712 --> 00:07:27.350
Oh. shit.

81
00:07:27.350 --> 00:07:28.318
And then when we were at the OB.

82
00:07:28.319 --> 00:07:32.618
I was jealous of everybody
because they were so happy.

83
00:07:32.619 --> 00:07:36.094
And I should be happy because
I know the baby is fine

84
00:07:36.095 --> 00:07:39.262
but everything is a mess.

85
00:07:39.263 --> 00:07:43.168
Work and this house
still isn't right.

86
00:07:43.531 --> 00:07:46.105
What are we gonna do. Norman?

87
00:07:46.402 --> 00:07:48.272
(CELLPHONE RINGING)

88
00:07:49.042 --> 00:07:50.703
I'm sorry. Hold on.

89
00:07:53.541 --> 00:07:55.246
What's this number?

90
00:07:55.609 --> 00:07:57.215
BELINDA: Hmm.

91
00:07:58.051 --> 00:07:59.481
(NORMAN GRUNTS)

92
00:08:00.449 --> 00:08:00.746
Hello?

93
00:08:00.747 --> 00:08:03.650
WOMAN: Norman.
Norman Gene. that you?

94
00:08:04.420 --> 00:08:06.487
(SUSPENSFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

95
00:08:06.488 --> 00:08:09.028
BELINDA: Uh... who's this?

96
00:08:09.029 --> 00:08:11.459
WOMAN: I am his mother.

97
00:08:11.460 --> 00:08:14.430
NORMAN: Jesus. Oh. my God.

98
00:08:18.401 --> 00:08:19.105
There are things

99
00:08:19.106 --> 00:08:21.568
I haven't told you
about Solange.

100
00:08:21.569 --> 00:08:23.273
Your... your stepmom?

101
00:08:23.274 --> 00:08:25.738
She's even worse than you think.

102
00:08:27.542 --> 00:08:29.312
She wouldn't let me eat...

103
00:08:29.313 --> 00:08:34.021
as a kid until she believed me
when I sang Jesus Loves Me.

104
00:08:36.188 --> 00:08:38.553
I don't know what's going on.

105
00:08:38.718 --> 00:08:41.192
My dad is dying.
Stomach cancer.

106
00:08:41.193 --> 00:08:42.193
(BELINDA GASPS)

107
00:08:42.194 --> 00:08:44.096
She wants me
to come see him. but...

108
00:08:44.097 --> 00:08:46.132
Norman. I am so sorry.

109
00:08:47.364 --> 00:08:49.431
- We have to see him.
- No.

110
00:08:49.432 --> 00:08:51.037
You have to. don't you?

111
00:08:51.038 --> 00:08:52.732
No. I don't!

112
00:08:55.174 --> 00:08:56.736
(NORMAN SIGHS)

113
00:09:00.047 --> 00:09:01.510
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

114
00:09:01.609 --> 00:09:03.643
She thinks that the Holy Spirit

115
00:09:03.644 --> 00:09:06.152
possesses her and...

116
00:09:07.186 --> 00:09:07.780
gives her power.

117
00:09:07.781 --> 00:09:11.652
She calls it
her signs and wonders.

118
00:09:12.422 --> 00:09:13.654
Wow.

119
00:09:14.160 --> 00:09:15.490
Why didn't you tell me?

120
00:09:15.491 --> 00:09:17.262
Because it's... it's...

121
00:09:18.065 --> 00:09:21.266
I thought
it would scare you away.

122
00:09:21.365 --> 00:09:24.136
And honestly.

123
00:09:24.137 --> 00:09:28.141
I don't think
that she would even...

124
00:09:30.374 --> 00:09:32.772
approve of you and me.

125
00:09:33.146 --> 00:09:37.150
- Oh. come on. She's not...
- I'm serious. It's like that.

126
00:09:37.447 --> 00:09:39.416
- (SIGHS)
- You know what?

127
00:09:40.219 --> 00:09:42.188
Solange doesn't matter.

128
00:09:44.520 --> 00:09:46.687
We have to focus on us.

129
00:09:48.524 --> 00:09:50.295
On our family.

130
00:09:50.724 --> 00:09:52.495
(BELINDA CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

131
00:09:52.660 --> 00:09:55.465
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS)

132
00:10:02.307 --> 00:10:04.738
(HEAVY BREATHING)

133
00:10:18.488 --> 00:10:20.424
(BABY CRYING)

134
00:10:21.623 --> 00:10:23.558
(CRYING CONTINUES)

135
00:10:23.559 --> 00:10:26.232
(HEARTBEAT POUNDING)

136
00:10:31.303 --> 00:10:33.436
(EERIE LULLABY MUSIC PLAYING)

137
00:10:33.437 --> 00:10:35.406
(BABY CONTINUES CRYING)

138
00:10:55.261 --> 00:10:57.163
(BELINDA GASPS)

139
00:10:57.164 --> 00:10:59.628
- NORMAN: Belinda?
- Norman.

140
00:10:59.925 --> 00:11:02.564
- NORMAN: You okay?
- (SIGHS)

141
00:11:02.565 --> 00:11:04.633
Guess I was sleepwalking.

142
00:11:06.338 --> 00:11:07.702
NORMAN: Oh.

143
00:11:08.373 --> 00:11:10.672
And did you open the window?

144
00:11:15.941 --> 00:11:18.911
(WINDOW CLOSES. LOCK CLICKS)

145
00:11:21.287 --> 00:11:22.617
That's Wallace's.

146
00:11:22.618 --> 00:11:24.422
I found it on the carpet.

147
00:11:26.490 --> 00:11:29.757
Must have missed it
when we moved the nursery.

148
00:11:30.824 --> 00:11:32.430
BELINDA: Yeah.

149
00:11:33.233 --> 00:11:35.433
(NORMAN SIGHS)

150
00:11:40.339 --> 00:11:43.210
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

151
00:11:57.851 --> 00:12:00.722
(EERIE VIOLIN MUSIC PLAYS
AND FADES)

152
00:12:04.396 --> 00:12:07.630
Do you know where he is. Mary?

153
00:12:07.729 --> 00:12:09.334
MARY: Oh. Ouch.

154
00:12:09.335 --> 00:12:10.896
I think
he's with the new hires...

155
00:12:10.897 --> 00:12:13.437
- (BELINDA SCOFFS)
- showing them around.

156
00:12:13.438 --> 00:12:15.407
But we had an appointment.

157
00:12:15.539 --> 00:12:16.969
(CLOCK TICKING)

158
00:12:17.541 --> 00:12:18.971
(BELINDA SIGHS)

159
00:12:23.448 --> 00:12:24.646
(BELINDA EXHALES)

160
00:12:24.647 --> 00:12:25.647
I'm done with this place.

161
00:12:25.648 --> 00:12:27.253
Wait. You can't go in there.

162
00:12:27.254 --> 00:12:29.619
- (DOOR SLAMS OPEN)
- BELINDA: I quit.

163
00:12:30.015 --> 00:12:31.653
(DOOR SLAMS SHUT)

164
00:12:31.654 --> 00:12:34.492
(PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

165
00:12:46.570 --> 00:12:49.408
(PIANO AND THEREMIN PLAYING)

166
00:12:49.705 --> 00:12:52.312
(DOOR OPENS. CLOSES)

167
00:12:55.447 --> 00:12:56.778
Norman.

168
00:13:03.950 --> 00:13:06.292
I was trying to buy
a can of paint today

169
00:13:06.293 --> 00:13:08.394
and the card declined.

170
00:13:08.856 --> 00:13:11.397
It was so embarrassing.

171
00:13:11.991 --> 00:13:15.335
What's going on? Are you okay?

172
00:13:19.933 --> 00:13:22.870
The pastor from
my parents' church called.

173
00:13:27.611 --> 00:13:29.041
My dad is dead.

174
00:13:32.517 --> 00:13:35.080
(CHURCH ORGAN PLAYING)

175
00:13:47.730 --> 00:13:50.436
(PRAYER BEING READ
INDISTINCTLY)

176
00:13:59.709 --> 00:14:01.809
PASTOR LEWIS:
Jesus said to her.

177
00:14:01.810 --> 00:14:05.450
- "He who believes in me..."
- (WHISPERS) Welcome.

178
00:14:05.451 --> 00:14:08.916
"Though he may die.
he shall live."

179
00:14:09.048 --> 00:14:10.488
Do you believe this?

180
00:14:10.489 --> 00:14:12.392
CONGREGATION: Yes.

181
00:14:12.557 --> 00:14:15.659
PASTOR LEWIS:
Death is a revelation.

182
00:14:15.857 --> 00:14:21.093
Lawrence Irwin is yet more alive

183
00:14:21.797 --> 00:14:23.799
than we are now.

184
00:14:25.097 --> 00:14:28.067
With his loving wife. Solange.

185
00:14:29.805 --> 00:14:31.642
He was teacher.

186
00:14:33.105 --> 00:14:34.744
healer.

187
00:14:35.646 --> 00:14:37.109
and friend.

188
00:14:38.946 --> 00:14:39.815
And...

189
00:14:39.816 --> 00:14:42.817
just in case any of you
sought one more lesson...

190
00:14:42.818 --> 00:14:44.523
(LAUGHTER)

191
00:14:45.524 --> 00:14:47.724
Lawrence instructed me

192
00:14:47.922 --> 00:14:51.727
to read his favorite passage
of scripture.

193
00:14:51.728 --> 00:14:58.636
(READS) "There is one body
and spirit who is above all"

194
00:14:58.966 --> 00:15:04.741
"and through all and in all."

195
00:15:07.744 --> 00:15:09.042
Norman.

196
00:15:10.879 --> 00:15:12.650
NORMAN: Pastor Lewis.

197
00:15:14.652 --> 00:15:17.621
Um. this is my wife.
uh. Belinda.

198
00:15:17.622 --> 00:15:19.118
Belinda. Hello.

199
00:15:19.987 --> 00:15:21.560
Oh.

200
00:15:21.692 --> 00:15:23.924
My condolences to you both.

201
00:15:23.925 --> 00:15:27.126
- Thank you for the service.
- PASTOR LEWIS: Oh.

202
00:15:28.534 --> 00:15:30.998
(CHUCKLING) Norman. wait.

203
00:15:32.065 --> 00:15:36.574
Uh. Solange. your mother.
asked me to bring you to her.

204
00:15:36.575 --> 00:15:37.740
- Stepmother.
- Yes.

205
00:15:37.741 --> 00:15:39.742
I understand your hesitation.

206
00:15:39.743 --> 00:15:41.480
I do. (INHALES SHARPLY)

207
00:15:41.481 --> 00:15:44.043
Not all of us believes
quite like she does.

208
00:15:44.044 --> 00:15:47.046
But. Norman. she's changed.

209
00:15:47.047 --> 00:15:49.522
- Oh. (CHUCKLES)
- PASTOR LEWIS: Yeah.

210
00:15:51.821 --> 00:15:53.460
Come and see.

211
00:15:58.157 --> 00:16:01.897
We both know what your father
would have prayed for.

212
00:16:01.996 --> 00:16:04.163
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

213
00:16:15.713 --> 00:16:17.616
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

214
00:16:17.781 --> 00:16:20.520
(SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES)

215
00:16:46.271 --> 00:16:48.108
(CANES CLACK LOUDLY)

216
00:16:48.614 --> 00:16:51.276
(FEET DRAGGING)

217
00:17:01.891 --> 00:17:03.760
SOLANGE: Would you
remove my veil

218
00:17:03.761 --> 00:17:06.797
so I could see you more clearly?

219
00:17:14.838 --> 00:17:17.576
You must be
my Norman's Belind-er.

220
00:17:17.577 --> 00:17:20.546
It's lovely to meet you.
Solange.

221
00:17:20.547 --> 00:17:23.615
He didn't say
you were expecting.

222
00:17:23.616 --> 00:17:24.111
And the pastor says

223
00:17:24.112 --> 00:17:26.816
the days of miracles
have come and gone.

224
00:17:26.817 --> 00:17:28.554
(CHUCKLES) Now. Solange...

225
00:17:28.555 --> 00:17:29.853
Hush now.

226
00:17:31.888 --> 00:17:34.726
(UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING)

227
00:17:38.961 --> 00:17:40.258
Is it a girl?

228
00:17:40.259 --> 00:17:41.633
Oh!

229
00:17:41.634 --> 00:17:43.635
Praise him! (CHUCKLES)

230
00:17:43.636 --> 00:17:45.670
How did...
how did you know that?

231
00:17:45.671 --> 00:17:50.005
Truth set aflame
by the Holy Spirit.

232
00:17:57.815 --> 00:18:00.620
Do I deserve any tenderness?

233
00:18:09.090 --> 00:18:11.729
We have much to discuss
as a family.

234
00:18:11.730 --> 00:18:13.632
(SPUTTERING) I... We. um...

235
00:18:13.633 --> 00:18:14.293
Belinda has to rest.

236
00:18:14.294 --> 00:18:16.767
Don't you owe me this kindness?

237
00:18:16.768 --> 00:18:19.331
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

238
00:18:21.300 --> 00:18:24.368
Ain't it a wonder
how you're changing?

239
00:18:24.369 --> 00:18:27.778
Sometimes I feel like
it's her body and not mine.

240
00:18:27.779 --> 00:18:29.780
You're a vessel
that holds his child.

241
00:18:29.781 --> 00:18:32.244
And praise Jesus.
he's making it right.

242
00:18:32.245 --> 00:18:34.752
Those two will never know
what it's like.

243
00:18:34.753 --> 00:18:37.788
- To change is woman.
- (BELINDA CHUCKLES)

244
00:18:37.789 --> 00:18:40.021
Well. Norman
is a wonderful husband.

245
00:18:40.022 --> 00:18:41.121
Like his father. bless him.

246
00:18:41.122 --> 00:18:43.288
but men are children
that must be taught.

247
00:18:43.289 --> 00:18:45.323
especially those
younger than us.

248
00:18:45.324 --> 00:18:46.226
I will admit.

249
00:18:46.227 --> 00:18:49.668
my last change
was not preferable.

250
00:18:49.669 --> 00:18:51.263
Men-o-pause.

251
00:18:51.264 --> 00:18:52.330
(LAUGHTER)

252
00:18:52.331 --> 00:18:54.200
Ain't no pause in it. (LAUGHS)

253
00:18:54.201 --> 00:18:57.940
Lucifer couldn't have made
hot flashes so hot.

254
00:18:57.941 --> 00:19:00.041
- (LAUGHTER)
- Okay. Okay. Stop.

255
00:19:00.042 --> 00:19:03.341
How's it look?
Had my lawyer draft the will.

256
00:19:03.342 --> 00:19:05.211
Of course.
he couldn't have done as well

257
00:19:05.212 --> 00:19:06.311
as my son. the lawyer.

258
00:19:06.312 --> 00:19:08.654
I'm a public defender. Solange.

259
00:19:08.655 --> 00:19:09.754
- I'm not probate.
- Of course.

260
00:19:09.755 --> 00:19:12.856
Helping those in need.
Taught him so well.

261
00:19:12.857 --> 00:19:15.892
You wanna give us everything?

262
00:19:15.893 --> 00:19:16.861
SOLANGE: Every cent.

263
00:19:16.862 --> 00:19:21.965
And I already sold the house.
so add that too.

264
00:19:22.163 --> 00:19:23.703
Well...

265
00:19:24.000 --> 00:19:25.066
Where... where are you
going to live?

266
00:19:25.067 --> 00:19:29.367
Well. doctor says I should not
live by my lonesome.

267
00:19:29.368 --> 00:19:32.975
PASTOR LEWIS: Norman.
your father's final request

268
00:19:32.976 --> 00:19:37.981
was that I help this decision.

269
00:19:38.377 --> 00:19:40.081
(EXHALES HEAVILY)

270
00:19:40.082 --> 00:19:43.690
He wants you to take
your mother into your home.

271
00:19:44.251 --> 00:19:47.221
(UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING)

272
00:19:50.092 --> 00:19:52.456
- So... What?
- Oh. don't you get it?

273
00:19:52.457 --> 00:19:54.898
(CHUCKLES)
I'm willing to give you

274
00:19:54.899 --> 00:19:57.033
all the money I got.

275
00:19:59.233 --> 00:20:00.233
(EXHALES)

276
00:20:00.234 --> 00:20:03.138
Is it a... a large...

277
00:20:10.882 --> 00:20:14.445
SOLANGE: All I ask in return
is you take me home.

278
00:20:14.446 --> 00:20:15.787
to live my final days

279
00:20:15.788 --> 00:20:19.187
on this fallen world
with my family.

280
00:20:19.319 --> 00:20:21.155
(MUSIC BUILDS. STOPS ABRUPTLY)

281
00:20:21.156 --> 00:20:22.156
Shit.

282
00:20:22.157 --> 00:20:24.257
Look. Solange is right.

283
00:20:24.258 --> 00:20:25.357
We can't live in the past.

284
00:20:25.358 --> 00:20:27.898
She was an awful mother to me...

285
00:20:27.899 --> 00:20:29.999
stepmother to me as a kid.

286
00:20:30.000 --> 00:20:30.803
The only TV I could watch

287
00:20:30.804 --> 00:20:32.496
was one goddamn tape
of VeggieTales

288
00:20:32.497 --> 00:20:34.267
because Nick Jr. was ungodly.

289
00:20:34.268 --> 00:20:36.874
VeggieTales?
Definitely after my time.

290
00:20:36.875 --> 00:20:40.207
But look. grown-up Norman
needs our help now.

291
00:20:40.208 --> 00:20:42.506
Yeah. No.
I... I... I don't know.

292
00:20:42.507 --> 00:20:44.310
Look. I couldn't buy
a can of paint.

293
00:20:44.311 --> 00:20:47.082
All I know is
if she comes to the house.

294
00:20:47.083 --> 00:20:49.117
it's gonna be
her fucking church.

295
00:20:49.118 --> 00:20:50.118
We're gonna be her disciples

296
00:20:50.119 --> 00:20:51.087
like her little
fucking apostles.

297
00:20:51.088 --> 00:20:53.319
No. We're gonna be
the ones that help her.

298
00:20:53.320 --> 00:20:56.058
Isn't it good
that it helps us too?

299
00:20:56.059 --> 00:20:59.061
I mean. we can pay off
the house with that money.

300
00:20:59.062 --> 00:21:01.393
Everything in me
is telling me to run away.

301
00:21:01.394 --> 00:21:03.329
To go and forget about her.

302
00:21:03.330 --> 00:21:06.871
Then do what she did. Change.

303
00:21:06.872 --> 00:21:08.940
It's not just about us.

304
00:21:09.908 --> 00:21:11.338
(NORMAN SIGHS)

305
00:21:13.175 --> 00:21:14.439
(OBJECT THUDS)

306
00:21:14.440 --> 00:21:17.376
Use your legs to lift.
Norman Gene.

307
00:21:17.377 --> 00:21:20.985
- I am.
- Did you tip the driver?

308
00:21:21.183 --> 00:21:24.219
- (CLICKING TONGUE)
- (NORMAN GRUNTS)

309
00:21:24.549 --> 00:21:26.121
Oh. Lord.

310
00:21:26.122 --> 00:21:27.221
BELINDA: Oh. yeah.

311
00:21:27.222 --> 00:21:29.355
Oh. Lord! (GROANS)

312
00:21:29.356 --> 00:21:31.093
BELINDA:
It's a really old house.

313
00:21:31.094 --> 00:21:33.558
- (SOLANGE SIGHS)
- BELINDA: Well...

314
00:21:34.097 --> 00:21:35.097
welcome home. Solange.

315
00:21:35.098 --> 00:21:38.001
- Thank you.
- How do you feel?

316
00:21:38.002 --> 00:21:38.431
Pooped.

317
00:21:38.432 --> 00:21:42.534
Let's get you to your room.
Right this way.

318
00:21:43.502 --> 00:21:45.107
- Here.
- Oh. where are we going?

319
00:21:45.108 --> 00:21:47.472
Oh. your room is upstairs
across from ours

320
00:21:47.473 --> 00:21:48.342
in case you need anything.

321
00:21:48.343 --> 00:21:50.409
I... I can't
get up them stairs.

322
00:21:50.410 --> 00:21:52.983
The doctor says it's arthritis.

323
00:21:52.984 --> 00:21:54.182
We made it up for you.

324
00:21:54.183 --> 00:21:57.054
Don't matter. I can't do it.

325
00:21:59.254 --> 00:22:01.123
Well. what's in there?

326
00:22:01.124 --> 00:22:02.587
Oh. that's the...

327
00:22:03.423 --> 00:22:04.555
That is the baby's room.

328
00:22:04.556 --> 00:22:06.932
BELINDA: Yeah.
That's the nursery.

329
00:22:07.867 --> 00:22:11.596
Ain't it unsafe
to have a baby downstairs?

330
00:22:11.838 --> 00:22:15.039
- BELINDA: Oh. well. I. uh...
- No.

331
00:22:15.567 --> 00:22:17.205
Belinda...

332
00:22:17.206 --> 00:22:20.374
Belinda put a lot of work
into that nursery.

333
00:22:20.473 --> 00:22:22.144
BELINDA: Uh. Norman.

334
00:22:22.145 --> 00:22:24.851
let's just talk about it
for a second.

335
00:22:25.214 --> 00:22:28.953
I thought
that we wanted the baby

336
00:22:28.954 --> 00:22:29.548
away from Wallace's room.

337
00:22:29.549 --> 00:22:33.089
I thought that's why we put
the nursery in the front room.

338
00:22:33.090 --> 00:22:34.420
I did. and I do.

339
00:22:34.421 --> 00:22:35.389
But she has a point.

340
00:22:35.390 --> 00:22:37.324
Isn't it dangerous
to keep a baby downstairs?

341
00:22:37.325 --> 00:22:40.492
They don't care
about their poor crippled...

342
00:22:40.493 --> 00:22:42.032
Oh. Jesus. Solange. please.

343
00:22:42.033 --> 00:22:44.133
Did you hear what he called me?

344
00:22:44.134 --> 00:22:45.431
He never calls me mother.

345
00:22:45.432 --> 00:22:48.104
Wouldn't it make you
feel terrible?

346
00:22:48.105 --> 00:22:49.468
Look. Let's just do it.

347
00:22:49.469 --> 00:22:50.338
I don't want her hearing us

348
00:22:50.339 --> 00:22:53.539
talking about Wallace
or asking questions.

349
00:22:55.343 --> 00:22:58.214
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

350
00:23:03.318 --> 00:23:06.189
(OBJECT CLATTERING)

351
00:23:06.519 --> 00:23:07.552
(NORMAN GROANS)

352
00:23:07.553 --> 00:23:09.995
He never liked chores.

353
00:23:10.457 --> 00:23:11.589
Hmm.

354
00:23:11.590 --> 00:23:15.626
When Lawrence and I finished
our home. we knew.

355
00:23:15.627 --> 00:23:19.003
Buy cheap. Buy twice.

356
00:23:19.004 --> 00:23:20.467
BELINDA: Okay.

357
00:23:21.171 --> 00:23:22.204
Oh. my God.

358
00:23:22.205 --> 00:23:23.403
Is this you. Solange?

359
00:23:23.404 --> 00:23:26.208
(CHUCKLES)
Hard to believe. ain't it?

360
00:23:26.209 --> 00:23:29.112
- Were you a model?
- And an actress.

361
00:23:29.113 --> 00:23:31.675
At least
that's what I called myself.

362
00:23:31.676 --> 00:23:34.513
I have no shame
in saying I was...

363
00:23:34.514 --> 00:23:35.547
(COUGHS)

364
00:23:35.548 --> 00:23:38.088
(COUGHS. SPUTTERS) I was...

365
00:23:38.089 --> 00:23:40.355
(WHEEZING COUGH)

366
00:23:42.192 --> 00:23:43.556
(SPUTTERING)

367
00:23:44.623 --> 00:23:46.426
I was beautiful.

368
00:23:46.427 --> 00:23:48.033
(SOLANGE LAUGHS)

369
00:23:48.165 --> 00:23:48.627
I knew it.

370
00:23:48.628 --> 00:23:51.167
Trouble is.
the photographer knew it too.

371
00:23:51.168 --> 00:23:54.038
and he knew what all men know.

372
00:23:54.039 --> 00:23:54.501
Hmm.

373
00:23:54.502 --> 00:23:57.338
Stopped my ambition right quick.

374
00:23:57.339 --> 00:23:59.109
Well. then why did you keep it?

375
00:23:59.110 --> 00:24:00.572
Do I seem like the kind of woman

376
00:24:00.573 --> 00:24:03.675
to run and hide from her past?
Hmm.

377
00:24:04.709 --> 00:24:06.447
BELINDA: Hmm.

378
00:24:08.317 --> 00:24:10.253
(PAPER RUSTLING)

379
00:24:20.230 --> 00:24:23.298
- Who're they?
- BELINDA: Oh. from my work.

380
00:24:23.299 --> 00:24:26.070
The one in the middle
could be Inanna.

381
00:24:26.071 --> 00:24:27.665
but no one knows.

382
00:24:27.666 --> 00:24:30.207
Didn't Norman say
they fired you?

383
00:24:31.373 --> 00:24:32.604
No. I quit.

384
00:24:32.605 --> 00:24:35.212
- It was my choice.
- Well...

385
00:24:36.213 --> 00:24:39.414
my work is in the Spirit.
Belind-er.

386
00:24:40.217 --> 00:24:41.987
And the Bible says.

387
00:24:41.988 --> 00:24:47.422
we are the house
that the Spirit lives in.

388
00:24:49.193 --> 00:24:52.031
I know how to make it right.

389
00:24:55.199 --> 00:24:56.134
NORMAN: All done.

390
00:24:56.135 --> 00:24:58.003
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

391
00:24:58.004 --> 00:25:00.698
SOLANGE: Looks like
a room for a baby.

392
00:25:00.699 --> 00:25:01.304
Well. yeah.

393
00:25:01.305 --> 00:25:03.305
We still have to move
a couple things around.

394
00:25:03.306 --> 00:25:06.506
but your bed's in there.
made up nice.

395
00:25:06.507 --> 00:25:08.079
(SOLANGE GRUNTS)

396
00:25:08.080 --> 00:25:10.478
I see you kept that chair.

397
00:25:12.579 --> 00:25:14.251
(CANE THWACKS)

398
00:25:15.054 --> 00:25:16.780
NORMAN: It... it was my mom's.

399
00:25:16.781 --> 00:25:20.058
(SPUTTERS) That's...
It's... It isn't yours.

400
00:25:20.059 --> 00:25:23.095
But it's in my room.
Norman Gene.

401
00:25:23.722 --> 00:25:25.163
Hmm.

402
00:25:29.761 --> 00:25:32.202
What would you say
to my purchasing

403
00:25:32.203 --> 00:25:34.138
new furniture for you?

404
00:25:34.139 --> 00:25:35.337
Oh. Solange. that's not...

405
00:25:35.338 --> 00:25:38.076
If this house
is to have a child.

406
00:25:38.077 --> 00:25:40.541
it must be properly furnished.

407
00:25:41.047 --> 00:25:41.476
The whole house?

408
00:25:41.477 --> 00:25:45.414
I'm sure you won't be able
to resist my offer for long.

409
00:25:46.349 --> 00:25:49.088
(PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

410
00:25:57.723 --> 00:25:59.527
(TOILET FLUSHING)

411
00:26:02.233 --> 00:26:03.696
(DOOR CREAKING)

412
00:26:23.155 --> 00:26:24.419
Norman Gene.

413
00:26:24.420 --> 00:26:26.388
- What?
- Who will say Grace?

414
00:26:26.389 --> 00:26:28.456
I would have thought
I taught you better.

415
00:26:28.457 --> 00:26:30.491
NORMAN: Solange.
we don't really do that here.

416
00:26:30.492 --> 00:26:32.394
No. It's all right. Norman.

417
00:26:32.395 --> 00:26:35.365
We should celebrate
everyone's faith.

418
00:26:40.733 --> 00:26:42.537
(NORMAN SIGHS)

419
00:26:50.314 --> 00:26:51.612
Oh. me.

420
00:26:51.810 --> 00:26:53.515
Okay. um...

421
00:26:54.186 --> 00:26:55.517
Well...

422
00:26:55.682 --> 00:27:00.323
it's wonderful that we can be
together as a family.

423
00:27:00.324 --> 00:27:03.491
And I'm most grateful
for our child

424
00:27:03.492 --> 00:27:05.856
to have a grandmother
here at home.

425
00:27:05.857 --> 00:27:08.893
In Jesus' name. amen.

426
00:27:09.168 --> 00:27:12.303
Thank you. I really love you.

427
00:27:21.180 --> 00:27:22.148
How do you like the ham?

428
00:27:22.149 --> 00:27:23.709
Norman said it's your favorite.

429
00:27:23.710 --> 00:27:25.348
Salty.

430
00:27:25.349 --> 00:27:27.317
- Why would you say that?
- It's the truth. ain't it?

431
00:27:27.318 --> 00:27:29.220
Just because it's true doesn't
mean you have to say it.

432
00:27:29.221 --> 00:27:31.421
- Wait. Is it salty?
- I won't lie.

433
00:27:32.884 --> 00:27:35.193
- Maybe a bit.
- See? (CHUCKLES)

434
00:27:35.194 --> 00:27:39.198
The Lord detests lying lips.
Norman Gene.

435
00:27:42.267 --> 00:27:42.663
(SOLANGE GRUNTS)

436
00:27:42.664 --> 00:27:47.601
I have realized I do not know
my granddaughter's name.

437
00:27:47.602 --> 00:27:51.506
Oh. we're gonna name her Fern.

438
00:27:51.507 --> 00:27:51.936
Fern?

439
00:27:51.937 --> 00:27:54.641
Is that a plant you got
growing in there?

440
00:27:54.642 --> 00:27:56.775
(LAUGHS) No.

441
00:27:56.776 --> 00:28:01.615
Used to be parents understood
names gotta have power.

442
00:28:01.616 --> 00:28:02.748
How about a family name?

443
00:28:02.749 --> 00:28:05.289
Well. my mother's name
was Ger-trude.

444
00:28:05.290 --> 00:28:06.917
(MIMICS PRONUNCIATION)
Ger-trude?

445
00:28:06.918 --> 00:28:08.721
I thought you all were
supposed to have

446
00:28:08.722 --> 00:28:10.228
more interesting names.

447
00:28:10.229 --> 00:28:11.427
What is that supposed to mean?

448
00:28:11.428 --> 00:28:13.462
I... I'm not trying
to be insulting.

449
00:28:13.463 --> 00:28:14.892
No. I wanna know what...

450
00:28:14.893 --> 00:28:16.795
what is a more interesting name?

451
00:28:16.796 --> 00:28:17.500
(CHUCKLES)

452
00:28:17.501 --> 00:28:19.600
Your father. what was his name?

453
00:28:19.601 --> 00:28:22.570
Walter. But I didn't
know him really well.

454
00:28:22.571 --> 00:28:25.540
Hmm. we call that
a broken family.

455
00:28:25.541 --> 00:28:27.509
Solange. would you please stop?

456
00:28:27.510 --> 00:28:29.611
BELINDA: They were academics.

457
00:28:29.908 --> 00:28:31.876
My dad did not leave.

458
00:28:31.877 --> 00:28:33.746
He died after I was born.

459
00:28:33.747 --> 00:28:36.617
I see. Mmm-hmm.

460
00:28:36.618 --> 00:28:37.915
Thank you for educating me

461
00:28:37.916 --> 00:28:40.258
and I apologize for any offense.

462
00:28:40.259 --> 00:28:42.557
but I am determined

463
00:28:42.558 --> 00:28:44.725
to give that child

464
00:28:45.627 --> 00:28:47.398
a proper name.

465
00:28:49.466 --> 00:28:51.996
(RECITING PRAYER IN TONGUES)

466
00:29:04.580 --> 00:29:05.383
(IN ENGLISH) Walter.

467
00:29:05.384 --> 00:29:08.011
Wally. Wally. Wally.
Wally. Wally.

468
00:29:08.012 --> 00:29:13.291
Wally. Wally. Wally. Wally.
Wally. Wally. Wally...

469
00:29:13.292 --> 00:29:15.327
(SLURPS) Wallace.

470
00:29:15.558 --> 00:29:18.659
(CONTINUES SPEAKING
IN TONGUES)

471
00:29:18.660 --> 00:29:19.858
(IN ENGLISH)
Wallace. nah. nah...

472
00:29:19.859 --> 00:29:22.399
What's that name
coming to me. Jesus...

473
00:29:22.400 --> 00:29:25.568
(CONTINUES SPEAKING
IN TONGUES)

474
00:29:30.870 --> 00:29:32.673
(EXHALES HEAVILY)

475
00:29:32.674 --> 00:29:33.938
(IN ENGLISH) Lawrence!

476
00:29:33.939 --> 00:29:36.710
Thank you. Lord! That's it!

477
00:29:36.711 --> 00:29:37.415
(SOLANGE CHUCKLES)

478
00:29:37.416 --> 00:29:40.450
You must name her
after her grandfather.

479
00:29:40.451 --> 00:29:42.650
What a fitting tribute.
Norman Gene.

480
00:29:42.651 --> 00:29:47.325
Of course. we must adjust
the name to fit the gender.

481
00:29:47.326 --> 00:29:48.789
How about...

482
00:29:49.856 --> 00:29:52.594
Little Laurie Irwin.

483
00:29:52.595 --> 00:29:53.497
(CHUCKLES)

484
00:29:53.498 --> 00:29:56.302
Oh. what do you think.
Belind-er?

485
00:29:57.402 --> 00:30:00.064
- Laurie.
- Ah! Yes.

486
00:30:08.644 --> 00:30:11.449
(FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING)

487
00:30:22.526 --> 00:30:25.529
(INDISTINCT PRAYING
IN TONGUES)

488
00:30:32.437 --> 00:30:33.966
(BELINDA GASPS)

489
00:30:35.407 --> 00:30:36.671
SOLANGE: Wallace...

490
00:30:36.672 --> 00:30:37.640
(GASPS)

491
00:30:37.641 --> 00:30:39.972
(PRAYING IN TONGUES CONTINUES)

492
00:30:50.620 --> 00:30:51.522
(BABY CRYING)

493
00:30:51.523 --> 00:30:54.085
(SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING)

494
00:30:54.822 --> 00:30:57.395
(SOLANGE CONTINUES
PRAYING IN TONGUES)

495
00:30:57.396 --> 00:30:57.957
(BABY CRYING)

496
00:30:57.958 --> 00:31:00.893
SOLANGE: (IN ENGLISH)
Help me. Jesus. Wallace.

497
00:31:00.894 --> 00:31:03.468
(BABY'S HEART BEATS RAPIDLY)

498
00:31:07.472 --> 00:31:09.408
(BABY CONTINUES CRYING)

499
00:31:15.942 --> 00:31:17.845
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

500
00:31:20.848 --> 00:31:22.784
(NORMAN GROANS SOFTLY)

501
00:31:29.021 --> 00:31:31.056
Baby. what are you doing up?

502
00:31:32.992 --> 00:31:34.994
BELINDA: I thought I was...

503
00:31:35.764 --> 00:31:37.634
I thought I was dreaming.

504
00:31:37.865 --> 00:31:39.933
Oh. well. come back.

505
00:31:40.439 --> 00:31:41.968
Come back to bed.

506
00:31:44.806 --> 00:31:47.875
How does Solange
know about Wallace?

507
00:31:48.480 --> 00:31:51.813
(SNIFFLES) Baby. who knows?

508
00:31:55.113 --> 00:31:58.523
Just... I wouldn't let her
get to you.

509
00:32:07.466 --> 00:32:09.962
(VINTAGE MUSIC
PLAYING ON RADIO)

510
00:32:09.963 --> 00:32:12.196
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

511
00:32:14.572 --> 00:32:18.509
MALE SINGER ON RADIO:
♪ Kneel down by the side ♪

512
00:32:18.510 --> 00:32:22.107
♪ Of your mother. my boy ♪

513
00:32:26.749 --> 00:32:28.652
BELINDA: Solange.

514
00:32:33.085 --> 00:32:34.757
BELINDA: Solange.

515
00:32:37.122 --> 00:32:38.695
Solange?

516
00:32:43.128 --> 00:32:44.635
