took the cross.

1021
01:00:55.621 --> 01:00:57.425
We named the baby.

1022
01:01:01.330 --> 01:01:02.561
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

1023
01:01:02.562 --> 01:01:04.498
SOLANGE: Help me!

1024
01:01:08.238 --> 01:01:09.832
Help me!

1025
01:01:09.833 --> 01:01:12.208
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1026
01:01:12.209 --> 01:01:13.473
Norman.

1027
01:01:13.474 --> 01:01:14.937
Belinda!

1028
01:01:15.179 --> 01:01:19.579
Anybody... Please.

1029
01:01:19.711 --> 01:01:22.581
M. E. double S. Mess.

1030
01:01:22.582 --> 01:01:25.683
I'm an M. E. double S. Mess.

1031
01:01:25.684 --> 01:01:28.291
- (GASPS)
- (LINE RINGING)

1032
01:01:29.688 --> 01:01:31.590
(RETCHES)

1033
01:01:31.591 --> 01:01:33.295
BELINDA: Listen.
you need to come home.

1034
01:01:33.296 --> 01:01:35.726
I don't care what excuse
you give your clients

1035
01:01:35.727 --> 01:01:36.365
or the court.

1036
01:01:36.366 --> 01:01:37.959
- I am losing my freaking mind.
- (BABY LAURIE WAILING)

1037
01:01:37.960 --> 01:01:40.401
NORMAN: Listen. just...
calm down. okay?

1038
01:01:40.402 --> 01:01:42.469
Norman.
I just cleaned up so much shit

1039
01:01:42.470 --> 01:01:44.867
while Solange just sat there
smiling at me.

1040
01:01:44.868 --> 01:01:47.903
- Jesus.
- I can't keep Laurie safe.

1041
01:01:47.904 --> 01:01:48.904
Do you hear her?

1042
01:01:48.905 --> 01:01:50.378
No. What... what's going on?

1043
01:01:50.379 --> 01:01:53.348
I can't do this by myself.
Your stepmother is...

1044
01:01:53.349 --> 01:01:55.548
- (CANE TAPS)
- (FEET SHUFFLING)

1045
01:01:55.549 --> 01:01:56.286
Hello?

1046
01:01:56.287 --> 01:01:57.781
- (CANES TAPPING)
- Belinda?

1047
01:01:57.782 --> 01:01:59.486
- (FEET SHUFFLING)
- Belinda. look...

1048
01:01:59.487 --> 01:02:00.619
I... I don't know
what's happening.

1049
01:02:00.620 --> 01:02:04.557
But I'll leave right now.
I'll be right there. Hello?

1050
01:02:04.558 --> 01:02:07.296
(SOLANGE SPEAKING
IN TONGUES)

1051
01:02:07.297 --> 01:02:10.333
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1052
01:02:14.931 --> 01:02:17.538
(BREATH TREMBLING)

1053
01:02:20.277 --> 01:02:22.411
(SHEEP BLEATING)

1054
01:02:27.680 --> 01:02:29.010
(BABY LAURIE COOING)

1055
01:02:29.011 --> 01:02:31.585
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC BUILDING)

1056
01:02:32.322 --> 01:02:34.291
(BABY LAURIE COOING)

1057
01:02:41.859 --> 01:02:43.497
(IN ENGLISH)
What'd you do to her?

1058
01:02:43.498 --> 01:02:45.829
Jesus was baptized.

1059
01:02:45.830 --> 01:02:50.570
And heaven opened.
and He saw the spirit of God.

1060
01:02:50.571 --> 01:02:54.002
- Stay away from her.
- Laurie is a child of God.

1061
01:02:54.003 --> 01:02:56.378
Laurie is my daughter.

1062
01:02:56.379 --> 01:02:57.808
(SOLANGE CACKLES)

1063
01:02:57.809 --> 01:02:59.546
I am her mother.

1064
01:02:59.547 --> 01:03:03.517
Oh. no. ya ain't.
Oh. no. ya ain't!

1065
01:03:03.518 --> 01:03:05.982
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES)

1066
01:03:06.488 --> 01:03:08.720
It was John
who was filled with the spirit

1067
01:03:08.721 --> 01:03:09.820
of his mother's womb.

1068
01:03:09.821 --> 01:03:11.855
She knew to fear the Lord.

1069
01:03:11.856 --> 01:03:12.988
Do you fear Him?

1070
01:03:12.989 --> 01:03:15.331
- No.
- Then fear me.

1071
01:03:15.332 --> 01:03:16.728
(LAUGHS)

1072
01:03:16.729 --> 01:03:18.532
Fear is the beginning
of knowledge.

1073
01:03:18.533 --> 01:03:21.568
It's fools like you despise
wisdom and my instruction.

1074
01:03:21.569 --> 01:03:24.934
Can't even feed that child
properly. can ya? I can.

1075
01:03:24.935 --> 01:03:27.706
And she will suckle
from my wisdom

1076
01:03:27.707 --> 01:03:30.478
as will Norman Gene
and the whole

1077
01:03:30.479 --> 01:03:32.040
- God-fearing world!
- (CANES CLATTER)

1078
01:03:32.041 --> 01:03:32.877
Get away from me.

1079
01:03:32.878 --> 01:03:36.484
Never! I called out to you.
Belinda.

1080
01:03:36.485 --> 01:03:37.947
I stretched out my hand

1081
01:03:37.948 --> 01:03:40.785
and I tried to teach you. but...

1082
01:03:40.786 --> 01:03:41.984
(SPEAKS IN TONGUES)

1083
01:03:41.985 --> 01:03:44.855
(IN ENGLISH) I will laugh when
your fear turns to destruction

1084
01:03:44.856 --> 01:03:48.397
and to a great wind and there
will be nothing left of you

1085
01:03:48.398 --> 01:03:49.893
but fear and anguish.

1086
01:03:49.894 --> 01:03:52.094
(SPEAKS IN TONGUES)

1087
01:03:53.436 --> 01:03:54.766
(IN ENGLISH)
I'll be there laughing

1088
01:03:54.767 --> 01:03:56.339
when you will call to the Lord

1089
01:03:56.340 --> 01:03:57.736
and he will not listen.

1090
01:03:57.737 --> 01:03:58.968
For then. finally.

1091
01:03:58.969 --> 01:04:01.608
you will be filled
with the mother's wisdom.

1092
01:04:01.609 --> 01:04:04.545
And we all know
who the real mother is.

1093
01:04:04.546 --> 01:04:06.382
- No!
- Yeah. go on. hit me!

1094
01:04:06.383 --> 01:04:07.713
Yeah. hit me!

1095
01:04:07.714 --> 01:04:09.848
(SOLANGE CACKLES)

1096
01:04:12.455 --> 01:04:14.423
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC BUILDING)

1097
01:04:14.424 --> 01:04:16.657
- (LOUD THUD)
- (SOLANGE GRUNTS)

1098
01:04:18.054 --> 01:04:20.397
(SOLANGE GROANS)

1099
01:04:21.497 --> 01:04:22.959
(SPUTTERING)

1100
01:04:22.960 --> 01:04:25.027
(LAUGHS CUNNINGLY)

1101
01:04:25.028 --> 01:04:28.537
(LAUGHS HEARTILY)

1102
01:04:31.540 --> 01:04:33.442
- (DOOR CLOSES)
- NORMAN: Belinda!

1103
01:04:33.443 --> 01:04:36.038
BELINDA: Norman!
She's out of control.

1104
01:04:36.039 --> 01:04:36.875
NORMAN: What is happening?

1105
01:04:36.876 --> 01:04:39.041
(SOBS) You gotta help me.
Norman Gene.

1106
01:04:39.042 --> 01:04:40.878
She's trying to murder me!

1107
01:04:40.879 --> 01:04:41.879
What? Norman.
I didn't do that!

1108
01:04:41.880 --> 01:04:42.913
NORMAN:
Belinda. look at her face!

1109
01:04:42.914 --> 01:04:44.849
Oh. I think she has to go
to the hospital.

1110
01:04:44.850 --> 01:04:47.622
- Come on. Okay. come here.
- (SOLANGE SOBBING)

1111
01:04:48.084 --> 01:04:49.921
(CONTINUES SOBBING)

1112
01:04:50.460 --> 01:04:52.054
NORMAN: It's okay.
It's all right.

1113
01:04:52.055 --> 01:04:53.826
(SOLANGE SOBBING)

1114
01:04:56.730 --> 01:04:58.864
(BABY LAURIE CRYING)

1115
01:05:00.635 --> 01:05:02.406
NORMAN: Belinda.

1116
01:05:02.967 --> 01:05:04.507
Belinda.

1117
01:05:05.101 --> 01:05:06.640
Belinda.

1118
01:05:06.641 --> 01:05:09.742
I've been screaming your name.
Do you not hear Laurie?

1119
01:05:09.743 --> 01:05:12.448
I'm trying the "crying it out"
method.

1120
01:05:12.449 --> 01:05:13.713
Isn't she a little young
for that?

1121
01:05:13.714 --> 01:05:15.583
She won't attach to me.

1122
01:05:15.584 --> 01:05:18.718
Do you think I wanna hear her
crying and crying?

1123
01:05:18.719 --> 01:05:19.719
(SHATTERING)

1124
01:05:19.720 --> 01:05:21.689
(BABY LAURIE CRYING)

1125
01:05:22.987 --> 01:05:24.659
I'm sorry.

1126
01:05:25.561 --> 01:05:26.122
Norman...

1127
01:05:26.123 --> 01:05:28.596
She said that you hit her.

1128
01:05:28.597 --> 01:05:29.960
I didn't. She's lying.

1129
01:05:29.961 --> 01:05:32.864
She told the nurses
that her daughter-in-law

1130
01:05:32.865 --> 01:05:33.602
put her in the hospital.

1131
01:05:33.603 --> 01:05:37.000
- You don't believe that.
- I... I took care of it.

1132
01:05:37.001 --> 01:05:38.034
No. She is going after me.

1133
01:05:38.035 --> 01:05:40.476
You are the one
who wanted her here

1134
01:05:40.477 --> 01:05:42.709
unless we're not being
very honest with ourselves.

1135
01:05:42.710 --> 01:05:45.206
You have never been honest
with me about your family.

1136
01:05:45.207 --> 01:05:47.208
First Solange.
and now your sister.

1137
01:05:47.209 --> 01:05:50.553
Your dead sister. Margaret-Anne.

1138
01:05:51.147 --> 01:05:52.180
My dead sister?

1139
01:05:52.181 --> 01:05:53.687
Yes. Solange said
she had a daughter.

1140
01:05:53.688 --> 01:05:54.656
Baby. what are you
talking about?

1141
01:05:54.657 --> 01:05:56.085
- And she passed away.
- Is this like postpartum stuff

1142
01:05:56.086 --> 01:05:58.792
- or maybe stuff about Wallace?
- Don't try to...

1143
01:05:59.661 --> 01:06:01.927
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

1144
01:06:02.191 --> 01:06:03.697
Oh. my God.

1145
01:06:03.698 --> 01:06:07.030
The hospital suggested that
because she's on bed rest...

1146
01:06:07.031 --> 01:06:09.065
- We need to hire a nurse.
- A nurse?

1147
01:06:09.066 --> 01:06:10.066
Or put her in a home
or something.

1148
01:06:10.067 --> 01:06:12.035
- (WHISTLE BLOWING)
- I won't do this by myself.

1149
01:06:12.036 --> 01:06:13.608
- Belinda. please.
- No.

1150
01:06:13.609 --> 01:06:15.544
I'm so close
to getting this job.

1151
01:06:15.545 --> 01:06:17.238
I just need a little more time.

1152
01:06:17.239 --> 01:06:19.042
Just be here with Laurie.

1153
01:06:19.043 --> 01:06:21.044
I'm here with Solange. Norman.

1154
01:06:21.045 --> 01:06:22.584
- (WHISTLE BLOWING)
- Please.

1155
01:06:22.585 --> 01:06:25.653
If I can just get over
this hump. it'll be different.

1156
01:06:25.654 --> 01:06:28.954
- (BABY LAURIE CRYING)
- (WHISTLE BLOWING FRANTICALLY)

1157
01:06:30.153 --> 01:06:31.890
(CRYING CONTINUES)

1158
01:06:31.891 --> 01:06:33.761
I'm doing diapers now.

1159
01:06:34.223 --> 01:06:35.697
Adult.

1160
01:06:37.193 --> 01:06:38.193
(DOOR CLOSES)

1161
01:06:38.194 --> 01:06:40.196
(BABY LAURIE CONTINUES CRYING)

1162
01:06:40.537 --> 01:06:43.166
(FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING)

1163
01:06:48.809 --> 01:06:51.515
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1164
01:07:05.529 --> 01:07:08.026
(BED CREAKING)

1165
01:07:13.229 --> 01:07:16.099
(THIS LITTLE LIGHT OF MINE BY
THE GATEWAY SINGERS PLAYING)

1166
01:07:16.100 --> 01:07:18.069
(SOLANGE GRUNTING)

1167
01:07:23.272 --> 01:07:24.911
(CRYING)

1168
01:07:27.980 --> 01:07:29.850
(WHISTLE BLOWING)

1169
01:07:30.147 --> 01:07:31.620
(BLOWS WHISTLE)

1170
01:07:31.621 --> 01:07:33.281
(SPRAY HISSING)

1171
01:07:33.282 --> 01:07:34.722
(CRYING)

1172
01:07:34.723 --> 01:07:36.593
(LAUGHS)

1173
01:07:37.594 --> 01:07:39.090
(BLOWS WHISTLE)

1174
01:07:40.091 --> 01:07:42.632
(SOLANGE SOBBING)

1175
01:07:43.666 --> 01:07:45.161
- (LAUGHS)
- (CRIES)

1176
01:07:45.162 --> 01:07:46.801
(BLOWS WHISTLE)

1177
01:07:48.968 --> 01:07:50.870
- (LAUGHS)
- (CRIES)

1178
01:07:50.871 --> 01:07:53.004
- (WHISTLE BLOWS)
- (CRIES)

1179
01:07:53.005 --> 01:07:54.874
(SOLANGE GRUNTS. MUTTERS)

1180
01:07:54.875 --> 01:07:56.139
- (CRIES)
- (LAUGHS)

1181
01:07:56.140 --> 01:07:58.009
(BLOWS WHISTLE)

1182
01:07:58.010 --> 01:07:58.879
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1183
01:07:58.880 --> 01:08:01.882
(WHISTLE BLOWING FRANTICALLY)

1184
01:08:04.313 --> 01:08:06.755
(WHISTLE CONTINUES BLOWING)

1185
01:08:09.791 --> 01:08:12.761
- (DOORBELL RINGS)
- (EXHALES)

1186
01:08:16.259 --> 01:08:17.358
(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)

1187
01:08:17.359 --> 01:08:19.130
Hello. Belinda.

1188
01:08:19.295 --> 01:08:21.968
Uh. Solange asked me to come.

1189
01:08:25.939 --> 01:08:28.039
(DOOR CREAKS SHUT)

1190
01:08:28.040 --> 01:08:28.777
Okay.

1191
01:08:28.778 --> 01:08:32.373
Uh. she said things
were getting a little tense.

1192
01:08:32.374 --> 01:08:34.618
- Hmm.
- Is that true?

1193
01:08:34.816 --> 01:08:37.147
It's just that
Norman is barely here

1194
01:08:37.148 --> 01:08:42.119
and Laurie doesn't even eat
unless it's from a bottle.

1195
01:08:42.120 --> 01:08:44.254
which they say is fine.

1196
01:08:45.189 --> 01:08:48.059
but I just feel like
a terrible mother.

1197
01:08:48.060 --> 01:08:50.227
You named your daughter Laurie?

1198
01:08:50.931 --> 01:08:53.031
- After Lawrence.
- (CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

1199
01:08:53.032 --> 01:08:55.066
She suggested it.

1200
01:08:55.067 --> 01:08:58.036
- Then Solange is helping.
- No. She's evil.

1201
01:08:58.037 --> 01:09:00.203
- Solange?
- Yes. Solange.

1202
01:09:00.204 --> 01:09:03.712
Look. she wants to take over
this house.

1203
01:09:03.713 --> 01:09:07.045
I mean. she...
she... she does things.

1204
01:09:07.046 --> 01:09:10.313
She has power over people.
I mean. you're...

1205
01:09:10.984 --> 01:09:12.887
you're right here.

1206
01:09:14.317 --> 01:09:15.923
You see this?

1207
01:09:18.090 --> 01:09:19.090
Two packs a day.

1208
01:09:19.091 --> 01:09:21.731
Can you guess
what got me to quit?

1209
01:09:22.765 --> 01:09:26.967
It was Solange and Lawrence
that laid hands on me.

1210
01:09:27.231 --> 01:09:29.134
and. well...

1211
01:09:30.399 --> 01:09:32.676
it was like a miracle.

1212
01:09:35.844 --> 01:09:36.976
So you believe like her?

1213
01:09:36.977 --> 01:09:39.143
I like to think
that I'm a Cessationist.

1214
01:09:39.144 --> 01:09:40.881
But Solange helped me.

1215
01:09:40.882 --> 01:09:42.278
(BELINDA SIGHS)

1216
01:09:42.279 --> 01:09:44.115
Well. so did Nicorette gum.

1217
01:09:44.116 --> 01:09:45.853
But the point is...

1218
01:09:45.854 --> 01:09:47.988
(CLOCK TICKING)

1219
01:09:49.451 --> 01:09:51.727
We all need
whatever help we can get

1220
01:09:51.728 --> 01:09:53.323
in this fallen world.

1221
01:09:55.259 --> 01:09:58.735
Is it worth
discriminating the source?

1222
01:10:01.166 --> 01:10:06.940
She thinks
that she is the only mother.

1223
01:10:06.941 --> 01:10:07.909
She wants to be a good mother.

1224
01:10:07.910 --> 01:10:10.042
She told me
that she fervently wishes

1225
01:10:10.043 --> 01:10:11.780
Norman knows she loves him.

1226
01:10:11.781 --> 01:10:14.113
- Bullshit.
- (SIGHS)

1227
01:10:14.982 --> 01:10:17.446
Can't we pray she meant it?

1228
01:10:19.019 --> 01:10:22.286
And she paid off
your mortgage. didn't she?

1229
01:10:22.451 --> 01:10:24.255
Isn't that proof?

1230
01:10:26.125 --> 01:10:27.489
BELINDA: No.

1231
01:10:28.490 --> 01:10:28.996
No.

1232
01:10:28.997 --> 01:10:32.064
Oh. Lord forgive me.
you didn't know.

1233
01:10:32.065 --> 01:10:35.001
- She shouldn't have done that.
- But you see...

1234
01:10:35.002 --> 01:10:37.433
- (BELINDA SOBS)
- even in secret...

1235
01:10:38.038 --> 01:10:40.776
Solange seeks to help you.

1236
01:10:40.777 --> 01:10:41.470
BELINDA: (SOBS) No.

1237
01:10:41.471 --> 01:10:44.307
It's a mother's blessing
to help her children.

1238
01:10:44.308 --> 01:10:46.244
- isn't it?
- (SOBS)

1239
01:10:46.750 --> 01:10:48.752
- (CLOCK CHIMING)
- Oh.

1240
01:10:49.918 --> 01:10:50.380
Don't forget.

1241
01:10:50.381 --> 01:10:53.889
what you and Norman
did for Solange is a...

1242
01:10:55.792 --> 01:10:57.222
a good deed.

1243
01:10:58.355 --> 01:11:00.225
(WHISTLE BLOWING)

1244
01:11:03.393 --> 01:11:05.967
(WHISTLE CONTINUES BLOWING)

1245
01:11:06.968 --> 01:11:09.905
(WHISTLE CONTINUES
BLOWING FAINTLY)

1246
01:11:10.235 --> 01:11:14.437
SOLANGE: Uh. I would like
to go to my chair.

1247
01:11:15.372 --> 01:11:18.012
That's why you called me
in here?

1248
01:11:18.144 --> 01:11:20.541
(DRAWN-OUT) Yes.

1249
01:11:20.542 --> 01:11:23.479
(STRAINING) Belinda.

1250
01:11:28.352 --> 01:11:31.256
(SOLANGE GROANS)

1251
01:11:33.489 --> 01:11:35.293
BELINDA: (SOFTLY) Okay.

1252
01:11:36.096 --> 01:11:37.492
I... I can't.

1253
01:11:37.493 --> 01:11:39.362
You can't or you won't?

1254
01:11:39.363 --> 01:11:41.233
(SOLANGE GROANS)

1255
01:11:42.399 --> 01:11:45.204
- (BOTH GRUNT)
- (SOLANGE BREATHES HEAVILY)

1256
01:11:45.468 --> 01:11:47.811
(SOLANGE CHUCKLES)

1257
01:11:49.076 --> 01:11:51.341
I'd know that look anywhere.

1258
01:11:51.342 --> 01:11:53.850
What's wrong. Belinda?

1259
01:11:54.081 --> 01:11:55.510
This is my house.

1260
01:11:55.511 --> 01:11:57.117
Of course.

1261
01:11:57.854 --> 01:11:59.548
between you and me.

1262
01:11:59.922 --> 01:12:02.385
But not according to the bank.

1263
01:12:02.386 --> 01:12:05.256
I'm just trying
to ease your burdens.

1264
01:12:05.257 --> 01:12:09.294
me and Norman Gene. together.

1265
01:12:15.168 --> 01:12:16.840
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

1266
01:12:18.600 --> 01:12:22.274
I'd like some water
before you go.

1267
01:12:23.143 --> 01:12:26.850
(DRAWN-OUT) Please.

1268
01:12:38.488 --> 01:12:41.194
Did you lie about your daughter?

1269
01:12:42.294 --> 01:12:45.165
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1270
01:12:50.038 --> 01:12:51.435
Hmm.

1271
01:12:52.403 --> 01:12:54.603
(GASPING)

1272
01:12:57.177 --> 01:12:58.881
(SPUTTERING)

1273
01:12:58.882 --> 01:13:00.950
(GASPING AND CHOKING)

1274
01:13:05.955 --> 01:13:08.353
(CHOKING)

1275
01:13:11.092 --> 01:13:13.127
(LAUGHS)

1276
01:13:20.068 --> 01:13:22.301
(CONTINUES LAUGHING)

1277
01:13:26.536 --> 01:13:29.209
SOLANGE: Help me. Norman Gene!

1278
01:13:30.342 --> 01:13:32.310
Please!

1279
01:13:32.311 --> 01:13:35.479
(SOLANGE CONTINUES
CALLING OUT INDISTINCTLY)

1280
01:13:36.150 --> 01:13:37.481
Don't.

1281
01:13:55.268 --> 01:13:58.040
- (SOLANGE MUTTERS)
- You're okay.

1282
01:13:58.304 --> 01:14:01.307
- (CANES TAPPING)
- (FEET SHUFFLING)

1283
01:14:03.078 --> 01:14:04.375
- It's okay.
- (GROANS)

1284
01:14:04.376 --> 01:14:06.179
Okay. I got you.

1285
01:14:06.180 --> 01:14:08.446
(SOLANGE CONTINUES GROANING)

1286
01:14:16.355 --> 01:14:19.226
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1287
01:14:32.404 --> 01:14:34.141
(NORMAN CRYING)

1288
01:14:34.142 --> 01:14:35.538
NORMAN: I want Mommy!

1289
01:14:35.539 --> 01:14:39.180
(HOLD FAST TO THE RIGHT
PLAYING ON RADIO)

1290
01:14:43.448 --> 01:14:46.351
♪ Kneel down by the side ♪

1291
01:14:46.352 --> 01:14:50.289
♪ Of your mother. my boy ♪

1292
01:14:50.290 --> 01:14:55.327
♪ You have only a moment
I know ♪

1293
01:14:55.328 --> 01:14:57.296
(DOOR CREAKING)

1294
01:14:57.297 --> 01:15:01.003
♪ But stay
Till I give you... ♪

1295
01:15:01.004 --> 01:15:03.699
(SUCKLING SOUNDS)

1296
01:15:05.008 --> 01:15:06.371
(SOFT MOANING)

1297
01:15:06.372 --> 01:15:08.538
(SUCKLING)

1298
01:15:08.539 --> 01:15:11.146
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES)

1299
01:15:13.214 --> 01:15:15.150
(SUCKLING SOUNDS)

1300
01:15:17.185 --> 01:15:18.615
(GASPS)

1301
01:15:27.723 --> 01:15:30.297
(MUSIC DISTORTS)

1302
01:15:32.464 --> 01:15:34.466
(RETCHES. GASPS)

1303
01:15:39.141 --> 01:15:40.538
NORMAN: Belinda?

1304
01:15:42.111 --> 01:15:43.442
Norman.

1305
01:15:45.345 --> 01:15:46.510
Did you hurt her?

1306
01:15:46.511 --> 01:15:48.182
(BABY LAURIE CRYING)

1307
01:15:48.183 --> 01:15:49.481
What?

1308
01:15:49.745 --> 01:15:51.648
Of course not.

1309
01:15:52.814 --> 01:15:55.751
(BABY LAURIE CONTINUES CRYING)

1310
01:15:56.092 --> 01:15:58.820
No. It wasn't...

1311
01:15:59.722 --> 01:16:00.393
I... I couldn't.

1312
01:16:00.394 --> 01:16:02.097
- Who was it then. Belinda?
- Solange!

1313
01:16:02.098 --> 01:16:03.197
Belinda.
she can't get up the stairs.

1314
01:16:03.198 --> 01:16:07.466
Yes. she can.
She doesn't need her canes.

1315
01:16:07.631 --> 01:16:10.501
She wants you to think
that it was me.

1316
01:16:10.502 --> 01:16:12.603
Just look.

1317
01:16:13.637 --> 01:16:15.309
Look.

1318
01:16:15.540 --> 01:16:18.708
It's missing teeth. Like her.

1319
01:16:20.248 --> 01:16:21.248
(EXHALES SOFTLY)

1320
01:16:21.249 --> 01:16:23.086
(CRYING CONTINUES)

1321
01:16:24.549 --> 01:16:26.617
She bit our baby.

1322
01:16:29.653 --> 01:16:31.424
(DOOR SQUEAKS)

1323
01:16:36.264 --> 01:16:38.496
SOLANGE: Norman. Norman Gene.

1324
01:16:38.497 --> 01:16:42.633
Is that you?
I can't see very clearly.

1325
01:16:43.337 --> 01:16:44.766
Has all this been pretend?

1326
01:16:44.767 --> 01:16:47.802
Oh-ho. you're with her.

1327
01:16:47.803 --> 01:16:51.378
- The one that hates me.
- Just stop!

1328
01:16:51.510 --> 01:16:54.215
You hurt Laurie
because you're trying

1329
01:16:54.216 --> 01:16:55.414
to turn me against Belinda.

1330
01:16:55.415 --> 01:16:57.185
Isn't that right? Admit it.

1331
01:16:57.186 --> 01:16:58.846
(LAUGHS)

1332
01:16:58.847 --> 01:17:00.552
(CACKLES)

1333
01:17:03.258 --> 01:17:05.491
Ain't me gotta confess.

1334
01:17:05.722 --> 01:17:06.657
I am your mother.

1335
01:17:06.658 --> 01:17:09.395
and I would never hurt
a child of God.

1336
01:17:09.396 --> 01:17:10.528
Jesus Christ!

1337
01:17:10.529 --> 01:17:13.169
Solange. you can't live
with us anymore.

1338
01:17:14.434 --> 01:17:18.537
You're tossing me
out of my own home.

1339
01:17:18.867 --> 01:17:21.639
after all I've done for you?

1340
01:17:24.444 --> 01:17:26.578
Come here. Norman Gene.

1341
01:17:29.581 --> 01:17:31.286
Come closer.

1342
01:17:37.721 --> 01:17:39.360
Come here.

1343
01:17:44.695 --> 01:17:46.268
Come closer.

1344
01:17:46.631 --> 01:17:48.699
(BED CREAKS)

1345
01:17:51.471 --> 01:17:52.802
(EXHALES)

1346
01:17:55.475 --> 01:17:57.213
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

1347
01:18:12.723 --> 01:18:14.361
SOLANGE: Why...

1348
01:18:14.362 --> 01:18:15.725
can't...

1349
01:18:15.726 --> 01:18:16.858
I...

1350
01:18:16.859 --> 01:18:18.795
die?

1351
01:18:20.863 --> 01:18:22.402
Why...

1352
01:18:22.403 --> 01:18:23.766
can't...

1353
01:18:23.767 --> 01:18:25.274
I...

1354
01:18:25.571 --> 01:18:27.705
die?

1355
01:18:28.310 --> 01:18:35.449
(SOBBING) Why can't I die?

1356
01:18:44.821 --> 01:18:46.888
(SUCKLING)

1357
01:18:46.889 --> 01:18:48.429
Norman!

1358
01:18:48.528 --> 01:18:49.792
Oh. my God. (CHUCKLES)

1359
01:18:49.793 --> 01:18:52.994
- Norman. She's doing it.
- (NORMAN GRUNTS)

1360
01:18:53.335 --> 01:18:54.864
She's eating.

1361
01:18:55.766 --> 01:18:57.504
(NORMAN SIGHS)

1362
01:18:57.801 --> 01:18:59.440
Thank God.

1363
01:19:28.029 --> 01:19:31.538
(I'M GONNA LIVE FOREVER
BY THE CATHEDRALS PLAYING)

1364
01:19:37.709 --> 01:19:41.680
♪ I'm gonna live forever ♪

1365
01:19:41.977 --> 01:19:45.618
♪ I'm gonna die. no. never ♪

1366
01:19:45.849 --> 01:19:48.818
♪ Jesus died
On a tree for me ♪

1367
01:19:48.819 --> 01:19:50.721
PASTOR LEWIS:
Death is a revelation.

1368
01:19:50.722 --> 01:19:53.989
♪ I'm gonna live forever ♪

1369
01:19:54.759 --> 01:19:58.466
♪ I'm gonna live forever ♪

1370
01:19:58.961 --> 01:20:02.701
PASTOR LEWIS:
He who believes in me...

1371
01:20:06.474 --> 01:20:08.069
though he may die.

1372
01:20:08.806 --> 01:20:10.973
he shall live.

1373
01:20:12.645 --> 01:20:14.779
Do you believe this?

1374
01:20:15.615 --> 01:20:19.750
♪ Hung in lights
Upon a marquee ♪

1375
01:20:19.751 --> 01:20:21.719
♪ Because Jesus Christ... ♪

1376
01:20:21.720 --> 01:20:23.326
(MUSIC STOPS)

1377
01:20:24.954 --> 01:20:27.660
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

1378
01:20:29.662 --> 01:20:32.500
(SOLANGE'S LAUGHTER ECHOES)

1379
01:20:36.570 --> 01:20:38.506
(CAR ENGINE REVS)

1380
01:20:38.803 --> 01:20:40.805
(ENGINE CONTINUES REVVING)

1381
01:20:43.071 --> 01:20:45.875
(SOLANGE'S ECHOED LAUGHTER
BECOMES LOUDER)

1382
01:20:45.876 --> 01:20:48.615
(SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING)

1383
01:20:52.916 --> 01:20:55.820
- (BELINDA YELLS)
- (LAUGHTER CRESCENDOES)

1384
01:20:58.020 --> 01:20:59.758
(SILENCE FALLS)

1385
01:21:04.532 --> 01:21:06.435
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

1386
01:21:18.942 --> 01:21:21.681
(SOLEMN MUSIC PLAYING)

1387
01:21:28.754 --> 01:21:30.954
(BABY LAURIE COOING)

1388
01:21:35.827 --> 01:21:37.730
(BABY LAURIE COOS)

1389
01:21:43.065 --> 01:21:44.836
- Hello.
- Hey.

1390
01:21:47.806 --> 01:21:50.006
(NORMAN GROANS)

1391
01:21:50.105 --> 01:21:52.778
- Should have used my legs.
- (CHUCKLES)

1392
01:21:54.714 --> 01:21:56.110
You look beautiful. babe.

1393
01:21:56.111 --> 01:21:58.651
- Excited for this interview?
- I am.

1394
01:21:58.652 --> 01:22:00.422
They're offering
leave right away.

1395
01:22:00.423 --> 01:22:01.951
which would be amazing.

1396
01:22:01.952 --> 01:22:04.856
- NORMAN: Hi.
- (BABY LAURIE BABBLES)

1397
01:22:09.190 --> 01:22:11.499
And how are you two doing?

1398
01:22:11.500 --> 01:22:13.963
(CHUCKLES)
They like to do somersaults.

1399
01:22:13.964 --> 01:22:16.098
(BOTH LAUGH)

1400
01:22:16.934 --> 01:22:18.507
Twins.

1401
01:22:19.706 --> 01:22:21.575
I don't know
if I'm ready for this.

1402
01:22:21.576 --> 01:22:22.973
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

1403
01:22:28.682 --> 01:22:30.717
(PAPER RUSTLING)

1404
01:22:41.926 --> 01:22:44.599
- Do you feel weird?
- Hmm?

1405
01:22:46.062 --> 01:22:47.833
I don't know. like.

1406
01:22:48.768 --> 01:22:50.572
Solange and...

1407
01:22:50.935 --> 01:22:53.508
all of her money
paying for all this.

1408
01:22:53.509 --> 01:22:55.610
She got what she deserved.

1409
01:22:57.040 --> 01:22:58.778
Yeah. You're right.

1410
01:23:01.517 --> 01:23:02.979
I don't know
that I'll ever get over

1411
01:23:02.980 --> 01:23:04.751
what she did to Laurie.

1412
01:23:09.954 --> 01:23:11.560
And to you.

1413
01:23:19.997 --> 01:23:22.868
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1414
01:23:33.076 --> 01:23:36.519
- (CANES TAPPING)
- (FEET SHUFFLING)

1415
01:23:42.624 --> 01:23:44.923
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC FADES)

1416
01:23:48.025 --> 01:23:49.631
You all right?

1417
01:23:50.698 --> 01:23:52.128
Get rid of that.

1418
01:23:57.573 --> 01:24:00.642
(NO REGRETS
BY EDITH PIAF PLAYING)

1419
01:24:09.552 --> 01:24:14.853
♪ No. no regrets ♪

1420
01:24:14.854 --> 01:24:20.321
♪ No. I will have no regrets ♪

1421
01:24:20.761 --> 01:24:23.323
♪ All the things ♪

1422
01:24:23.324 --> 01:24:25.963
♪ That went wrong ♪

1423
01:24:25.964 --> 01:24:28.295
(SINGING ALONG)
♪ For at last ♪

1424
01:24:28.296 --> 01:24:32.299
♪ I have learned
To be strong ♪

1425
01:24:32.300 --> 01:24:38.008
♪ No. no regrets ♪

1426
01:24:38.009 --> 01:24:43.113
♪ No. I will have no regrets ♪

1427
01:24:43.652 --> 01:24:46.016
♪ For the grief ♪

1428
01:24:46.017 --> 01:24:48.755
♪ Doesn't last... ♪

1429
01:24:48.756 --> 01:24:50.218
ADMINISTRATOR:
Congratulations. Belinda.

1430
01:24:50.219 --> 01:24:53.859
Thank you.
The twins were a big surprise.

1431
01:24:53.860 --> 01:24:55.256
I mean. I love being a mom.

1432
01:24:55.257 --> 01:24:58.292
but the classroom
is where I'm supposed to be.

1433
01:24:58.293 --> 01:25:00.030
I mean. our kids have to see us

1434
01:25:00.031 --> 01:25:02.165
being happy and free. right?

1435
01:25:02.968 --> 01:25:03.606
And I am.

1436
01:25:03.607 --> 01:25:07.136
You know. I've never been
better in my entire life.

1437
01:25:07.137 --> 01:25:11.613
I feel like
no one can hold me back.

1438
01:25:11.614 --> 01:25:12.175
What do you mean?

1439
01:25:12.176 --> 01:25:15.045
Well. let's just say
being cooped up in a house

1440
01:25:15.046 --> 01:25:16.783
with a newborn
and a mother-in-law

1441
01:25:16.784 --> 01:25:18.114
can drive anyone crazy.

1442
01:25:18.115 --> 01:25:21.019
I can't imagine
how you handled it.

1443
01:25:21.822 --> 01:25:23.218
SOLANGE: Why...

1444
01:25:23.219 --> 01:25:24.890
can't...

1445
01:25:24.891 --> 01:25:25.924
I...

1446
01:25:25.925 --> 01:25:27.860
die?

1447
01:25:27.861 --> 01:25:34.967
(SOBBING) Why can't I die?

1448
01:25:35.099 --> 01:25:38.365
Why... can't...

1449
01:25:38.366 --> 01:25:40.741
I... die?

1450
01:25:40.742 --> 01:25:42.942
(NO REGRETS
BY EDITH PIAF CONTINUES)

1451
01:25:43.041 --> 01:25:44.778
Why...

1452
01:25:44.779 --> 01:25:46.307
can't...

1453
01:25:46.308 --> 01:25:49.948
I... die?

1454
01:25:49.949 --> 01:25:52.346
♪ All the things ♪

1455
01:25:52.347 --> 01:25:55.283
♪ That went wrong ♪

1456
01:25:55.284 --> 01:25:57.384
♪ For at last ♪

1457
01:25:57.385 --> 01:26:02.026
♪ I have learned
To be strong ♪

1458
01:26:02.027 --> 01:26:02.896
(THUDS)

1459
01:26:02.897 --> 01:26:05.128
(MUFFLED STRAINING)

1460
01:26:05.129 --> 01:26:07.328
♪ No regrets ♪

1461
01:26:07.329 --> 01:26:12.366
♪ No. I will have no regrets ♪

1462
01:26:12.367 --> 01:26:18.680
♪ For the seed that is new ♪

1463
01:26:18.681 --> 01:26:20.682
♪ It's the love... ♪

1464
01:26:20.683 --> 01:26:22.344
ADMINISTRATOR: Belinda?

1465
01:26:23.983 --> 01:26:29.252
♪ That is growing for you ♪

1466
01:26:34.158 --> 01:26:37.161
(SONG ENDS
WITH MUSICAL FLOURISH)

1467
01:26:39.966 --> 01:26:42.738
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

